  "texts": [
    "For the Traffic dataset, the model maintains an identical RMSE and MAE of 0.03 for both extreme and normal values, indicating consistent performance across all data points.",
    "In the Electricity dataset, the Hybrid Transformer records an extreme RMSE of 520.21 and an extreme MAE of 332.14, leading to a Total RMSE of 451.22 and a Total MAE of 376.28.",
    "ConclusionThis paper presents a novel framework called TXtreme, composed of multiple models, that better estimates rare but significant extreme values in time series to reduce overall forecasting errors.TXtreme captures extreme values that generally range between 5% to 15% in datasets, improving forecasting accuracy by 7% to 25%.",
    "Overall TXtreme model demonstrates exceptional generalization across multiple domains, effectively predicting extreme values and unseen data.",
    "It achieves superior or highly competitive performance in diverse datasets such as solar energy, traffic, electricity and web traffic, often outperforming other advanced models by addressing extreme values in time series data."
